cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.SD

The paper discusses the use of machine learning for procedural content generation, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The authors propose the use of discriminative models, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the modification of WaveFunctionCollapse, which is a graphics-related PCG approach (cs.GR). The authors mention the use of positive and negative examples, which suggests the possibility of using computer vision techniques for image recognition (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the interaction mode between the artist and the machine, which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SD).
